<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF986A27FD2795341A74BFC3" pageId="99" pageNumber="857" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF986A27FD2795341A74BFC3" blockId="99.[730,1322,798,1226]" lastBlockId="99.[112,1322,1232,2844]" pageId="99" pageNumber="857">
Previously listed as a race of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF986A27FB7395341B23B8BC" authorityName="H. Allen" authorityYear="1866" box="[1167,1315,877,910]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhogeessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="857" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parvula">R. parvula</taxonomicName>
. Until recently included 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF986A27FBB895CD1AE4B887" box="[1092,1252,916,949]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhogeessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="857" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bickhami">R. bickhami</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF986A27FD27959D1D89B8EF" box="[731,905,964,989]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhogeessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="857" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="menchuae">R. menchuae</taxonomicName>
, which were split based on mitochondrial and nuclear genetic distances; the distances between 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF986A27FB6592561B22BF1E" authorityName="H. Allen" authorityYear="1866" box="[1177,1314,1039,1068]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhogeessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="857" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tumida">R. tumida</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF986A27FD2792621D50BF66" authorityName="Goodwin" authorityYear="1958" box="[731,848,1083,1108]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhogeessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="857" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aenea">R. aenea</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF986A27FC5592621A54BF66" box="[937,1108,1083,1108]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhogeessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="857" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="menchuae">R. menchuae</taxonomicName>
were low, and suggest that the first two might be treated as synonyms, although karyological and morphological data do not support this; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF986A27FF8992891EE3BFC3" authorityName="Goodwin" authorityYear="1958" box="[117,227,1232,1265]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhogeessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="857" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aenea">R. aenea</taxonomicName>
appears to be the most recently evolved of the three. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF986A27FF8F92AE1B26BE2A" box="[115,1318,1271,1304]" pageId="99" pageNumber="857" type="distribution">
<caption id="90EB6676FF986A27FF8F92AE1B26BE2A" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6398246" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6398246" box="[115,1318,1271,1304]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6398246/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="857" targetBox="[115,707,806,1221]" targetPageId="99">
